</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF19FF53A7ADF8D3FC50DBE9" blockId="128.[189,1401,1852,2025]" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
The 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FF19FF53A7E3F8D3FE9CDB57" box="[243,346,1852,1878]" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">syntypes</typeStatus>
are lost, hence the diagnosis is based on the original description of 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF19FF53A36FF8D3FAB5DB57" author="Mello-Leitao C." box="[1151,1395,1852,1878]" firstAuthor="Mello-Leitao" journalOrPublisher="Archivos do Museu Nacional" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" pagination="7 - 72" part="33" refId="ref150843" refString="Mello-Leitao C. 1931. Pedipalpos do Brasil e algumas notas sobre a ordem. Archivos do Museu Nacional 33: 7 - 72." title="Pedipalpos do Brasil e algumas notas sobre a ordem" type="journal article" year="1931">Mello-Leitão (1931)</bibRefCitation>
. The median eyes were not described, but the species was collected in the Atlantic Forest and is not troglobitic; hence, it is assumed to possess a median ocular tubercle with median eyes. 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF19FF53A3CCF86AFEC8DBC5" author="Mello-Leitao C." firstAuthor="Mello-Leitao" journalOrPublisher="Archivos do Museu Nacional" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" pagination="7 - 72" part="33" refId="ref150843" refString="Mello-Leitao C. 1931. Pedipalpos do Brasil e algumas notas sobre a ordem. Archivos do Museu Nacional 33: 7 - 72." title="Pedipalpos do Brasil e algumas notas sobre a ordem" type="journal article" year="1931">Mello-Leitão (1931)</bibRefCitation>
described six dorsal spines on the pedipalp patella, but included the long setiferous tubercle in the count; the true count of dorsal spines on the patella is five.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
